value.0: Strath wore the dress of the Tethyrian Army and seemed to be around twenty five years old.
Armor and clothing of this type was produced during the Interregnum years. There was still a lot of it around.
In Tethyr, the longsword was considered a civilized weapon. This particular blade was enchanted to burn with flames so long as it is held.

This is a locking mechanism which can be incorporated into a gauntlet by an armorsmith. 

A gauntlet lock takes up 1/1 of the available modification slots for a gauntlet.

This is a soft ingot of golden alloy meant for gilding armor or a shield.

Gilding Gold takes up 1/2 of the available modification slots for an armor or shield.

This is a knotted leather cord which can be incorporated into a weapon pommel or shield grip by a tailor.

A Knotted Leather Cord takes up 1/2 of the available modification slots for a weapon or shield.

These are protective spikes which may be incorporated into an armor or shield by an armorsmith.

Protective Spikes take up 1/2 available modification slots.

This is a sacred pattern which may be incorporated in a cloak by a tailor.

A Sacred Pattern takes up 1/1 available modification slots.

Silmer's wick is composed of long fibrous red crystals which break down into a fine powder. Silmer's wick can be incoporated with a suit of armor or robes by a tailor to insulate against flames.

Silmer's Wick takes up 1/2 available modification slots.

This is a spool of iron wire which can be incorporated into a robe item by a tailor.

An Iron Wire Spool takes up 1/2 of the available modification slots for a robe.

This is a spool of steel wire which can be incorporated into a robe item by a tailor.

A Spool of Steel Wire takes up 1/2 of the available modification slots for a robe.
This well made bastard sword was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
Bastard swords are also known as hand-and-a-half swords, falling between the longsword and greatsword in length.
This oil can be applied to armor, imbuing it with the power of the Shield of Faith spell.
This odd potion invoked an abjuration effect that protects against evil.
This potion allowed the wearer to see very well in complete darkness, as the spell Ultravision.

This is a blessed reliquary, prepared for use by paladins to imbue their Holy Avengers.

A Blessed Reliquary takes up 1/10 available modification slots for a Holy Avenger.

Celestial Essence takes up 1/10 available modification slots for a Holy Avenger.

A Holy Chalice takes up 1/10 available modification slots.

This holy emblem contains formulas for destroying lycanthropes and is intended for paladins to use with their Holy Avengers.

A Holy Emblem uses 1/10 available modification slots.

These holy scriptures are filled with fables from the recent Time of Troubles.

If used by a cleric to bless armor or a shield, Holy Scriptures take up 1/2 available modification slots.

This sigil has interweaving patterns that repel creatures not native to the Prime Material plane.

If used by a cleric to bless an armor or shield, a Holy Sigil takes up 1/2 available modification slots.

This is Martyr's blood, which is reserved for use by paladins to grant their Holy Swords defending properties.

Martyr's Blood uses 1/10 available item slot modifications.

This is a Nirvana Codex, prepared for use by Paladins to align their Holy Avengers.

A Nirvana Codex takes up 1/10 available modification slots for a Holy Avenger.

These are Saint's Waters, specially prepared for paladins to use to additionally sanctify their Holy Avenger.

Saint's Water uses 1/10 available item slot modifications.

This shattered edge is from the steel of a Holy Avenger of a martyr. It is reserved for use by paladins to make their Holy Avengers more lethal.

A Shattered Edge takes up 1/10 available modification slots.

This Silver Dragon Eye is a beautiful diamond cut to perfection. It is intended for use by Paladins to enhance the damage dealt by their Holy Avengers.

A Silver Dragon Eye takes up 1/10 available modification slots.

This Starry Dew Gem is a beautiful sapphire cut to perfection. It is intended for use by Paladins to enhance the damage dealt by their Holy Avengers.

A Starry Dew Gem takes up 1/10 available modification slots.

As a follower of a specific deity there will be rites and practices associated with that deity. One thing that is common to all is the requirement to use the appropriate holy symbol when calling upon the deity's power. 

The Holy Symbol for each deity may be different and should be obtained from the appropriate temple. The holy symbol for a ranger or druid may be somthing sacred to the caster rather than a church sanctioned object.

This book contains a list of spells for which a practitioner must have a Holy Symbol equipped. 

In addition there are some spell which require other components. These are usually found in the same places arcane magic users obtain components.

This book is useful for Clerics, Druids, Rangers and Paladins.
